  "name": "Morrison COU2 VAD Hemolysis Credibility Assessment — Clean NC-9 Package",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Model inputs) carries explicitly-documented low confidence in the viscosity sub-model parameterization, with wide Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds (±18% on NIH hemolysis index). This limitation is fully disclosed in the rationale and uncertainty quantification records. The assessment team accepted the limitation as residual risk given conservative safety margins demonstrated across all 5 flow-speed operating points. Decision: Accepted with documented residual uncertainty.",
