      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "All model inputs characterized with probability distributions for Monte Carlo UQ (N=5000 samples). EXPLICITLY FLAGGED LOW-CONFIDENCE INPUT: Blood viscosity parameterization carries wide uncertainty (CV=14%) due to limited whole-blood rheology data at device-relevant shear rates above 5000 s⁻¹. This is the primary driver of the ±18% uncertainty bound on the hemolysis index. The limitation is fully documented in UQ record https://uofa.net/synth/uq/hemolysis-mc-uq-record. Despite this, the 97.5th-percentile upper bound of the hemolysis prediction (0.52 g/dL/100 L) remains 35% below the clinical threshold (0.80 g/dL/100 L), providing sufficient margin. All remaining inputs (geometry, rotational speed, inlet flow rate, outlet pressure) are characterized with high confidence (CV < 2%). Achieved level equals required level; limitation accepted as residual risk with documented margin justification."
    },
