  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels in every case. One explicitly-flagged limitation exists: the blood viscosity sub-model carries low confidence at shear rates > 5000 s⁻¹ (CV=14%), driving a ±18% uncertainty bound on the NIH hemolysis index. This limitation is fully documented in the Model Inputs factor rationale and in UQ record https://uofa.net/synth/uq/hemolysis-mc-uq-record. The assessment team reviewed the margin analysis: the 97.5th-percentile upper bound prediction of 0.52 g/dL/100 L provides a 35% margin below the clinical threshold of 0.80 g/dL/100 L at the worst-case operating point. This margin is deemed sufficient to absorb residual viscosity uncertainty without compromising patient safety. The limitation is accepted as documented residual risk. Provenance chain is complete: all ValidationResults link to experimental datasets, generating activities, and UQ records. The decision is grounded in the structured credibility evidence and the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification ensemble (N=5000). Decision: Accepted.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
